text.tspan: My heart is wounded—Lord, I pray
Thou know’st the pain of every scar,
And lonesome thoughts that come withal,
But know them not just from afar:
My heart’s true Friend, come bear them all!
If in my side a thorn must be,
If in my heart enduring pain,
Then may Thy peace be balm to me
And grace my weakness still sustain.
I bring Thee now, O Potter mine.
Fill with Thyself the breaches there—
